The inquiry into allegations of impropriety at the Public Investment Corporation continues on Wednesday. • Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - The inquiry into allegations of impropriety at the Public Investment Corporation continues on Wednesday. The commission will hear from businessman Jayendra Naidoo. His company, Lancaster, received R9.3-billion from the PIC to invest in Steinhoff. WATCH: Former board member testifies PIC inquiry On Tuesday, former PIC board member Sibusisiwe Zulu denied any wrongdoing. She was implicated in a series of emails by a whistleblower. Zulu says the accusations have taken a toll on her family.